25:33.165 --> 25:36.268
of an important
medical accessory.

25:36.268 --> 25:42.708
♪♪

25:42.708 --> 25:47.179
Hi. I'm Paige Brattin,
and I'm from Waimea, Hawaii,

25:47.179 --> 25:50.249
and I'm seeking $250,000

25:50.249 --> 25:52.518
for 10% equity
in my business.

25:52.518 --> 25:56.522
You see, Sharks,
when my daughter Eddy was 5,

25:56.522 --> 26:00.459
my whole world changed
when we found out she was blind.

26:00.459 --> 26:03.429
She was diagnosed
with refractive amblyopia,

26:03.429 --> 26:06.698
which is one of the leading
causes of childhood vision loss.

26:06.698 --> 26:08.700
And while it's likely
you've never heard of it,

26:08.700 --> 26:13.238
amblyopia shockingly affects
1 in 45 children.

26:13.238 --> 26:15.274
But, luckily, it's treatable

26:15.274 --> 26:17.376
by wearing an eye patch
over the stronger eye

26:17.376 --> 26:19.478
to strengthen the vision
of the weaker eye.

26:19.478 --> 26:21.313
But the existing patches
on the market

26:21.313 --> 26:24.249
were uninspiring,
uncomfortable,

26:24.249 --> 26:27.219
and really difficult
to convince children to wear.

26:27.219 --> 26:30.489
That's why I created
See Worthy Eye Patches.

26:30.489 --> 26:34.293
My innovated and patented design
has breathable materials,

26:34.293 --> 26:37.496
medical adhesives
that stick safely to the skin,

26:37.496 --> 26:39.631
and a whole-new shape
that fits the eye socket

26:39.631 --> 26:42.701
a lot more comfortably,
and fits infants to adults.

26:42.701 --> 26:45.637
I started See Worthy Patches
for my daughter Eddy,

26:45.637 --> 26:49.274
now a 14-year-old honors student
with strong vision

26:49.274 --> 26:51.410
and an even stronger
sense of self.

26:51.410 --> 26:54.279
So, you see, Sharks, I'm worthy.

26:54.279 --> 26:59.384
Who wants to help me
help others patch proudly?

26:59.384 --> 27:02.688
I love that you're bringing
dignity and joy and fun

27:02.688 --> 27:05.591
to what can really be
a tough situation for kids.

27:05.591 --> 27:09.361
Mm-hmm.
I know you said 1 in 45 kids,
but what does that equate to?

27:09.361 --> 27:12.197
So, that's about 2 million
children in the U.S. alone.

27:12.197 --> 27:14.500
Tell us when and how long

27:14.500 --> 27:17.169
the child has to
wear the patch to --

27:17.169 --> 27:18.203
That's a great question.

27:18.203 --> 27:21.106
So, each diagnosis
is different.

27:21.106 --> 27:23.275
Some kids have to wear
an eye patch

27:23.275 --> 27:26.411
for two hours a day
for six months.

27:26.411 --> 27:28.981
My daughter had to wear it
for eight hours a day

27:28.981 --> 27:29.615
for six years.

27:29.615 --> 27:32.618
I had to deal with patches
for my father all the time.

27:32.618 --> 27:35.354
When I was 11,
he lost his eye in an accident.

27:35.354 --> 27:38.156
He did upholstery on cars,
and a staple broke and hit him.

27:38.156 --> 27:40.459
So we lived with patches
all the time.

27:40.459 --> 27:41.627
This would have
been amazing.

27:41.627 --> 27:45.230
But there are others
out there, right?
Mm-hmm.

27:45.230 --> 27:47.332
And so, just what is
the industry?

27:47.332 --> 27:49.434
There's only one other
bigger,

27:49.434 --> 27:52.104
larger corporation/company
making these.

27:52.104 --> 27:53.906
Are they designed
like yours are?

27:53.906 --> 27:54.540
Do they have patterns?

27:54.540 --> 27:57.442
The traditional eye patch
is pear-shaped.

27:57.442 --> 28:00.612
So, this new shape is,
to me, everything,

28:00.612 --> 28:02.447
because the heavy lifting
of the adhesive

28:02.447 --> 28:04.383
goes up here,
where the skin is tougher,

28:04.383 --> 28:06.351
not in the sensitive
under-eye.

28:06.351 --> 28:08.287
And the shape -- the shape
isn't patented, though?

28:08.287 --> 28:09.388
