but through that entire period,

34:59.297 --> 35:01.533
I was a full-time student
and researcher,

35:01.533 --> 35:04.336
and I was still able
to increase my sales

35:04.336 --> 35:05.971
to a 3X year-over-year rate.

35:05.971 --> 35:07.272
Any repeat orders?

35:07.272 --> 35:10.342
Yes. So our repeat
customer order is 78%.

35:10.342 --> 35:11.476
[ Sharks exclaiming ]
Yes.

35:11.476 --> 35:14.245
Wow! Now, are these people
that are suffering from eczema,

35:14.245 --> 35:16.314
or are they just people
who love the smell of the soap?

35:16.314 --> 35:18.216
It's a mix of both.
I would say about, like,

35:18.216 --> 35:19.718
60-something percent
of our customers

35:19.718 --> 35:22.520
actually suffer from eczema,
psoriasis, sensitive skin.

35:22.520 --> 35:24.189
What did you do
last year?

35:24.189 --> 35:27.425
Yeah, so, last year,
we did $66,000 in sales.

35:27.425 --> 35:28.660
And did you make any money
off of that?

35:28.660 --> 35:32.364
Yeah. So, we are profitable.
We profited about $38,000.

35:32.364 --> 35:34.299
That's great.
What is your margin?

35:34.299 --> 35:38.103
So, they cost us $2.38
to manufacture and box,

35:38.103 --> 35:39.337
but we sell them for $11.

35:39.337 --> 35:40.271
Oh!
Wow!

35:40.271 --> 35:41.172
And that's for
a box of four?

35:41.172 --> 35:42.173
That's very good margin.

35:42.173 --> 35:43.708
No, $11 is one singular
bar soap.

35:43.708 --> 35:46.311
And you sell them individually
or in this box?
One bar?

35:46.311 --> 35:48.113
Yeah. So, you can do
the four for $40,

35:48.113 --> 35:49.080
